cspec
------------------------------------------
CSpec is a Behaviour-driven Development (http://behaviour-driven.org/)
framework for C.
It provides a spec framework for describing the behavior of the functions of
your system.
The syntax is inspired from RSpec (http://rspec.info/) to be as legible as
possible.
The source code is as portable and as light as possible to make it easy to run
the library  on embedded devices.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.35-1
  libcspec-devel-0.3.0snapshot+git20140225-1bl1
  libcspec0-0.3.0snapshot+git20140225-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-1
  cygport-0.18.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-3
  libtool-2.4.6-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/arnaudbrejeon/cspec

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/arnaudbrejeon/cspec.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack cspec-0.3.0snapshot+git20140225-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./cspec-0.3.0snapshot+git20140225-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/cspec-0.3.0snapshot+git20140225-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/cspec-0.3.0snapshot+git20140225-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcspec0-0.3.0snapshot+git20140225-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcspec-devel-0.3.0snapshot+git20140225-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

